                                           INTERNET
                                               │
                                 ┌──────────────────────────┐
                                 │ Xfinity Gateway / Modem │
                                 │ (Bridge Mode preferred) │
                                 └────────────┬─────────────┘
                                              │
                                   WAN        │
                              ┌───────────────▼───────────────┐
                              │       pfSense Firewall        │
                              │      + Suricata IDS/IPS       │
                              └───────────────┬───────────────┘
                                              │
                                         LAN / TRUNK
                                              │
                              ┌───────────────▼───────────────┐
                              │       Cisco L3 Switch         │
                              │   VLANs / Inter-VLAN paths    │
                              └──────┬────────┬────────┬──────┬────────┬────────┘
                                     │        │        │      │        │
                                     │        │        │      │        │
                                 VLAN 10   VLAN 20  VLAN 25 VLAN 30 VLAN 40  VLAN 666
                                Management   Home      IoT    Lab/SOC Guest    Malware
                                   Admin    Trusted Untrusted Servers/Test Temp  Isolated


VLAN 10 — MANAGEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Purpose:
- Administrative control plane

Devices:
- Your admin access
- pfSense management interface
- Cisco switch management interface

Access idea:
- Can manage other VLANs
- Other VLANs should not initiate access here


VLAN 20 — HOME
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Purpose:
- Trusted daily-use household network

Devices:
- Mom's PC
- Sister's laptop
- Trusted personal devices
- Your host laptop when using it normally

Access idea:
- Internet access allowed
- No direct access to management
- No access to malware zone
- Limited access to lab only when needed


VLAN 25 — IOT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Purpose:
- Low-trust smart devices

Devices:
- Smart TVs
- Alexa
- Smart bulbs
- Smart air purifier
- Smart light strip
- Other internet-connected home gadgets

Access idea:
- Internet access allowed
- Block access to Home VLAN by default
- Block access to Management VLAN
- Block access to Lab VLAN unless specifically required


VLAN 30 — LAB / SOC
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Purpose:
- Practice environment for IT, SOC, and server workflows

Systems:
- Splunk server
- Windows Server / Active Directory
- Jira
- Kali Linux VM
- OpenVAS
- Test PC
- Test printer
- Test phone
- Other lab VMs

Access idea:
- Internet access for updates/testing
- Internal communication for logs and domain services
- Restricted from Home VLAN unless explicitly allowed


VLAN 40 — GUEST / TEST
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Purpose:
- Temporary devices and non-trusted test access

Devices:
- Guest devices
- Temporary phones/laptops
- Quick test endpoints

Access idea:
- Internet only
- No internal VLAN access


VLAN 666 — MALWARE / HOT ZONE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Purpose:
- Quarantine zone for dangerous testing

Systems:
- Malware analysis VM
- Unsafe exploit/testing VM

Access idea:
- No access to internal VLANs
- No internet by default, or tightly controlled only if required
- Heavily monitored

             [Home VLAN] ----\
                               \
             [IoT VLAN] ------- > pfSense + Suricata ---> Splunk ---> Jira
                               /
             [Lab VLAN] -------/

             [Malware VLAN] --> tightly isolated, monitored separately
